We can see from the diagram clearly that the electric generator uses the rotating potted coil in a magnetic field to cause the change in magnetic flux and hence generates alternating current.
Then let's derive the formula of this process.
Form of Energy inputted: mechanic energy
Form of Energy outputted:electric energy

## Formula derivation
We assume that the rotating coil has a constant speed of rotation $\omega$
The magnetic flux is at maximum when the plane of action of coil is perpendicular to the magnetic induction line.
The magnetic fluc is at minimum when the plane of action of coil is parallel to the magnetic induction line.
We know that magnetic flux $\phi=BA$
and the voltage of the induced current 
$\epsilon=\frac{d\Phi}{dt}$
Formula:
$A=\sin(\omega t+\lambda)$
Hence:
$\phi=B\sin(\omega t+\lambda)$
$\epsilon=B\omega\cos(\omega t+\lambda)$
